12. Qf3 { Neccesary to remove Black's most important piece from the board. This move also leaves the f4-pawn weak, and this is our main target in order to get an advantage. } { 12.Nxb4?? would be a blunder due to 12...Qe3+ as it forces our king to go to the queenside, where it would be quite exposed to Black's attack. 13.Kc3 Bg7+ 14.Kb3 Qb6 15.Bxf4 a5 and Black has a winning attack. } Qxf3 
13. gxf3 Nxd5 
14. exd5 { Reaching an even endgame, but we have a very interesting idea to create problems to our opponent. } Rg8 
