8. Nc3 Qe7 
9. Be3 { My recommendation in the main course } Bxe3 { 9...Nxc3 is Black's best reply. } 
10. Qxe3 Nxc3 
11. Qxe7+ Kxe7 
12. bxc3 Bxc2 { After this sequence, Black gets the pawn. White, in return, has a great lead in development. } 
13. Kd2 Ba4 { 13...Bf5 14.Re1+ Kf6 15.Ne5 15...h5 16.h3 g6 17.Bc4 and White is clearly better. } 
14. Re1+ Kd6 { Black should have played 14...Kf8 keeping the king on the kingside to protect the pawns. } 
15. Ng5 Kxd5 { 15...Be8 } 
16. Re4 { White enters a winning sequence. } Be8 
17. Rd4+ Kc6 
18. Be2 Nd7 
19. Bf3+ Kb6 
